## Problem

`normalizeDiagnosticEventsModule` in `src/plugin-sdk/root-alias.cjs` hardcodes `mod.r` as the minified export alias for `onDiagnosticEvent`. The bundler reassigns single-letter aliases across builds — on 2026.5.25-beta.1, `r` is `emitFailoverEvent`, not `onDiagnosticEvent` (`u`).

This causes `TypeError: unsubscribeDiagnosticEvents is not a function` on every gateway stop/restart for any plugin that subscribes to diagnostic events via the SDK wrapper. Data collection works (the shared-state fallback path subscribes correctly), but the combo unsubscribe closure fails because `emitFailoverEvent(listener)` does not return a callable unsubscribe function.

## Change

Replace the hardcoded `mod.r` check with `Function.name` introspection:

```javascript
// Before — fragile, breaks when bundler reassigns 'r'
if (typeof mod.r === "function") {
  return { ...mod, onDiagnosticEvent: mod.r };
}

// After — survives alias changes across all builds
const fn = Object.values(mod).find(
  (v) => typeof v === "function" && v.name === "onDiagnosticEvent",
);
if (fn) {
  return { ...mod, onDiagnosticEvent: fn };
}
```

JavaScript functions retain their original `.name` property regardless of export aliasing, so this works on any build without tracking which letter the bundler assigns.

## Who benefits

Every plugin that uses `onDiagnosticEvent` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk` — currently the only known consumer is [henrikrexed/openclaw-observability-plugin](https://github.com/henrikrexed/openclaw-observability-plugin), but any future plugin using the diagnostic events API would hit the same issue.

## Why now

The alias mapping broke between 5.22 and 5.25 when the bundler reshuffled exports. This will break again on any future build that reassigns `onDiagnosticEvent` to a different letter — the `Function.name` approach is permanently stable.

## Test plan

- [ ] Gateway stop with otel-observability plugin: no `TypeError: unsubscribeDiagnosticEvents is not a function`
- [ ] Diagnostic event subscription still works (model.usage events reach plugin)
- [ ] Plugin unsubscribe on stop is clean (no leaked listeners)

Fixes #87082
